Package: jaid
Title: High-Performance Utilities for Data Analysis and Programming
Version: 0.0.0.9002
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Seokhoon", family = "Joo", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "seokhoonj@gmail.com")
Description: 'jaid' (J's Aid) is a functional toolkit designed for efficient 
    and reproducible programming. It provides high-performance utilities including 
    vector and matrix helpers, in-place transformations for 'data.table', and 
    advanced meta-programming tools such as argument capture and call tracing 
    (e.g., 'capture_names', 'trace_arg_expr'). Core helpers for insurance stay 
    data handling and preprocessing are also included, serving as a foundation 
    for more specialized analytical packages. Additional features include string 
    utilities for Japanese text (e.g., Zenkaku to Hankaku) and convenient I/O 
    wrappers. Selected routines are implemented in C for speed.
